news.title: Only six out of 83 Patna smart city projects completed in four years
news.para: Four years since its selection under the Smart Cities Mission (SCM) by the Centre, only 20% funds have been utilised and six out of the 83 projects could be completed under the Patna Smart City Limited (PSCL).

news.title: Karnataka government to study duty cut for all types of properties: R Ashoka
news.para: He reiterated that the government planned to reduce the guidance value (minimum selling price) of properties, adding that a decision would be made by December. He gave the assurances during a debate on the Karnataka Stamp (Amendment) Bill.

news.title: Chennai development body seals unauthorised constructions
news.para: ​Similarly, shops, an association room, a multi-purpose hall, aa gym and paying guest rooms were locked and sealed in multiple floors of an eight-storey building on the Tambaram-Velachery Main Road at Tambaram over construction violations.

news.title: Ahmedabad: Town planning services under one roof
news.para: The chairman, Devang Dani, said that town planning offices are situated at various places in the city and people have to run from one office to another to get their work done.

news.title: Gurugram: Sold sector 69 colony plots flouting rules, ex-MLA kin & 29 others face FIR
news.para: In the letter to the police on Monday, the DTCP stated that the 30 offenders must be made co-accused in an earlier FIR lodged against four persons, including the former Gurgaon legislator, for developing an illegal colony, ‘Avenue 69’, on a five-acre land in Sector 69 without mandatory permission from a competent authority.

news.title: Lavasa citizens depend on final bids for project revival
news.para: Delhi-based Srishti and Madhav Dhir and Darwin Platform Group are the two resolution applicants and have offered a two-part payment structure offering a similar upfront amount, followed by a phased disbursal of amount in a three-seven year period.

news.title: Gurugram: Illegal road, construction waste dumping on Aravali land near DLF-3
news.para: The area is categorised as ‘gair mumkin pahar’ (uncultivable hill) in revenue records and hence non-forest activities such as cutting of trees and constructions are not permitted.

news.title: Did you help real estate companies in bad phase, SC asks Noida bodies
news.para: The apex court was examining a joint plea filed by Noida and Greater Noida authorities to recall its order passed in June last year capping interest rate around 8%, instead of 15-23%.

news.title: Gujarat RERA extends deadline to file annual report
news.para: ​The last date for the submission has been extended till December 31, 2021, to provide relief to developers amid the disruptions caused by the Covid-19 pandemic.

news.title: About 350 lapsed projects up for scrutiny by MahaRERA
news.para: The MahaRERA had recently described 3,371 residential projects across the state as “lapsed projects” between 2017 and 2021 with the developers failing to complete them within the deadline.

news.title: Gurugram: Ardee City's builder booked for violating licence norms
news.para: ​The developer has also been accused of fraudulently showing a portion of land owned by the Haryana Shehri Vikas Pradhikaran (HSVP) as part of the township at the time of seeking the licence.

news.title: Consumer panel gives three-year jail to Supertech's MD
news.para: ​As a last chance, the bench of C Viswanath and R S R Maurya said the jail term will come into effect a week from September 20th if Supertech doesn’t deposit the money. Soon after the verdict on Monday, the developer moved the Delhi high court, which refused to interfere or stay the order.

news.title: Evergrande crisis shows cracks in China's property market
news.para: China’s Evergrande Group, the embattled property developer whose towering debt has set off panic in global markets, is buckling under the weight of more than $300 billion in debt.

news.title: BlackRock, HSBC among largest buyers of Evergrande debt: Morningstar
news.para: BlackRock added 31.3 million notes of Evergrande's debt between January and August 2021, pushing its stake in the company to 1% of the assets in its $1.7 billion Asian High Yield Bond Fund, according to Morningstar.

news.title: Evergrande's unit to make $35.9 million onshore coupon payment on Sept 23
news.para: Hengda Real Estate Group said in a statement it would make the coupon payment on its Shenzhen-traded 5.8% September 2025 bond on time on Sept. 23.
